## Problem

The README's [MCP Server section](https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/cass_memory_system#-mcp-server) shows this Claude Code configuration:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "cm": {
      "command": "cm",
      "args": ["serve"]
    }
  }
}
```

This implies `cm serve` works as a **stdio** MCP server. However, `cm serve` explicitly starts an HTTP-only server and rejects stdio:

```
[cm] MCP HTTP server listening on http://127.0.0.1:8765
[cm] WARNING: Transport is HTTP-only; stdio/SSE

cass returns hits array but cm expects groups array:

  cass returns:
  {
    "count": 2,
    "hits": [...]
  }

  cm expects:
  {
    "groups": [{ "sessions": [...] }]
  }
